      "message": "I understand the upside of having consistent descriptions for cgroups v1 and v2, however that opens up possibilities for conflicting definitions like in your example:\n\n\"Ggroups2\" : [\n       {\n          \"Controller\" : \"root\",\n          \"Path\": \"/dev/cg2_bpf\",\n          \"Mode\": 0600,\n          \"UID\": \"root\",\n          \"GID\": \"root\",\n       },\n       {\n          \"Controller\" : \"cpuset\",\n          \"Path\": \"/dev/cg2_bpf\",\n          \"Mode\": 0755,\n          \"UID\": \"system\",\n          \"GID\": \"system\",\n       },\n      ],\n\nNote that Mode, UID and GID for the same path are defined differently. That\u0027s why I think for Cgroupv2 with unified hierarchy it\u0027s more appropriate to have smth like this:\n\n\n\"Ggroups2\" : {\n          \"Path\": \"/dev/cg2_bpf\",\n          \"Mode\": 0600,\n          \"UID\": \"root\",\n          \"GID\": \"root\",\n          \"Controllers\" : [\n              \"Controller\": \"cpuset\",\n              \"Controller\": \"memory\"\n           ]\n},",
